<font color="#FF0000">BEST WISHES FOR THE NEW YEAR</font><br>
<tt>Mon Dec 23 16:21:17 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
To all of you who have read these dialog exchanges, and to all of you who have contributed (and who may contribute in the weeks to come)..... my very best wishes for a happy New Year.<br><br>
To the veterans and civilians on both sides of the war, whether American, Vietnamese, or other nationality... I, too, echo Arthur's wish for a new beginning.<br><br>
As the year winds down.... I request information on the following two items:<br><br>
Chronologies: does there exist on the web (or elsewhere) a detailed day-by-day chronology of events in southeast Asia after the Geneva conference? This can be reconstructed by using New York Times and London Times indexes, but then all the information would have to be re-typed. If you are an instructor and have taught about Viet Nam, and have used a detailed chronology, would you be willing to share it? and...<br><br>
Regarding Tet, 1968: In your opinion....<br><br>
1.Was media coverage of the Tet Offensive in 1968 (specifically television) balanced or not?<br><br>
2.If not balanced, in your opinion did the images favor South Vietnam or North Vietnam/VC?&quot; <br><br>
Regarding teaching this class....<br><br>
My students and I especially would like to hear from former American and Vietnamese Prisoners of War; from members of families with loved ones still listed as missing in action; from nurses and medical care staff; from Americans who were in Viet Nam during the last days of April, 1975; from veterans or civilians who were against the war; and from Americans who have traveled to Vietnam during the past 4-5 years; from Vietnamese-Americans (immigrants post 1975) who risked their lives for freedom in the U.S. <br><br>
Again, regards and best wishes..... for a happy New Year.
